blog.description: All things Marvel. Latest news or rumors. Predictions, speculations, and fancasts. OPEN FOR FAN CAST REQUESTS. Representation Matters.

summary:
Hercules to be introduced in the upcoming Eternals movie
While it has been reported that outside of the core group of characters...
body:
Rumor Roundup:

Hercules to be introduced in the upcoming Eternals movie

While it has been reported that outside of the core group of characters Star-Fox would be joining the franchise it was recently rumored that Hercules would also be making his MCU debut there. I often wondered that with all of the Disney Classic live action remakes would Hercules have a shared continuity or could their be two? (Same with Namor, the Little Mermaid, and Atlantis: The Lost Empire over Atlantis in which both concepts of Greek Mythology are shared among the DCEU’s current headliners Wonder Woman and Aquaman but I digress).

This is a rumor I’m intrigued by but is more than likely not to happen because of the reasons above as well as that the core Eternals already being enough of a number of characters to introduce in one film. However my fancasting heart couldn’t help but picture the massive man that is Joe Manganiello to play the legendary demigod. Yes he is currently supposed to be the DCEU’s Deathstroke Slade Wilson but there aren’t too many in Hollywood larger than Manganiello and with the charisma to match. Personally I’d prefer a tall dark handsome Greek actor but until further notice I like him for this pick. With Deathstroke suppose to play villain in the cancelled Ben Affleck Batfleck film perhaps he’s free to join the MCU or maybe join as the character in director James Gunn’s The Suicide Squad reboot (or BOTH!).
